# Web Application - Application Discovery

 Once the application mapping is done, the task of analyzing the applicationâ€™s
 functionalities can beging.
 The end goal is to identify the key attack surfaces the web application
 exposes and to begin to probe for exploitable vulnerabilities.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------


###### Debug parameters
Choose one or more functionalities where hidden debug parameters may be
implemented.
Use "Cluster bomb" attack type in Burp Intruder and the following common debug
parameter names with common values (such as true, yes, on, and 1):
```
debug
test
hide
hidden
source
```
For POST requests, supply the parameter in both the URL query string and the
request body.
